method, whether you

00:28:49.810 --> 00:28:52.060 align:middle line:84%
are studying geology, or
mathematics, or physics,

00:28:52.060 --> 00:28:54.640 align:middle line:84%
or whatever, goes through
the following stages.

00:28:54.640 --> 00:28:56.943 align:middle line:84%
You start off by making
observations in your field,

00:28:56.943 --> 00:28:58.360 align:middle line:84%
whatever your field
happens to be.

00:28:58.360 --> 00:29:00.130 align:middle line:90%
You collect your data.

00:29:00.130 --> 00:29:03.550 align:middle line:84%
You begin to see possible
patterns in your data.

00:29:03.550 --> 00:29:06.460 align:middle line:84%
That creates a hypothesis to
explain the possible pattern.

00:29:06.460 --> 00:29:07.900 align:middle line:90%
Now, you've got to test that.

00:29:07.900 --> 00:29:09.250 align:middle line:90%
You got empirically test that.

00:29:09.250 --> 00:29:12.640 align:middle line:84%
So you set up an experiment to
test if the hypothesis explains

00:29:12.640 --> 00:29:13.840 align:middle line:90%
the putative pattern.

00:29:13.840 --> 00:29:16.570 align:middle line:84%
If it does, it has to be
replicated by somebody else

00:29:16.570 --> 00:29:18.738 align:middle line:84%
to make sure it wasn't a
statistical aberration.

00:29:18.738 --> 00:29:21.280 align:middle line:84%
If the other person says, yeah,
we got the same results, now,

00:29:21.280 --> 00:29:23.260 align:middle line:84%
you have a principle
established in the field.

00:29:23.260 --> 00:29:25.900 align:middle line:84%
Now, a bunch of principles
create a model of the field.

00:29:25.900 --> 00:29:28.660 align:middle line:84%
But inevitably, there
will be new anomalous data

00:29:28.660 --> 00:29:29.680 align:middle line:90%
present themselves.

00:29:29.680 --> 00:29:31.360 align:middle line:84%
And now, you have to
tweak the old model

00:29:31.360 --> 00:29:33.140 align:middle line:90%
to accommodate the new data.

00:29:33.140 --> 00:29:36.460 align:middle line:84%
And at some stage, so
many anomalous data points

00:29:36.460 --> 00:29:37.300 align:middle line:90%
present themselves.

00:29:37.300 --> 00:29:38.800 align:middle line:84%
