00:43:27.360 --> 00:43:30.682 align:middle line:84%
So I'll tell you a story from
my own tradition in Ireland.

00:43:30.682 --> 00:43:32.640 align:middle line:84%
There's a tradition in
Ireland, particularly up

00:43:32.640 --> 00:43:34.300 align:middle line:90%
into the 1940s and 1950s.

00:43:34.300 --> 00:43:36.090 align:middle line:90%
I was born in 1946.

00:43:36.090 --> 00:43:40.990 align:middle line:84%
And all fires were trough fires,
what you might call pit fires--

00:43:40.990 --> 00:43:41.790 align:middle line:90%
pit.

00:43:41.790 --> 00:43:42.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Pit, yes, pit.

00:43:42.430 --> 00:43:42.540 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:43:42.540 --> 00:43:44.290 align:middle line:84%
>>O'LAORIE: We call
the trough in Ireland.

00:43:44.290 --> 00:43:46.080 align:middle line:90%
So all fires were trough fires.

00:43:46.080 --> 00:43:48.210 align:middle line:84%
At night, when the
family went to bed,

00:43:48.210 --> 00:43:50.550 align:middle line:84%
the mother would be the
last person to go to bed.

00:43:50.550 --> 00:43:53.040 align:middle line:84%
And she would take
the fire, wreck it,

00:43:53.040 --> 00:43:54.780 align:middle line:90%
put all the embers together.

00:43:54.780 --> 00:43:59.350 align:middle line:10%
And she'd put the dust
over the top of it,

00:43:59.350 --> 00:44:01.350 align:middle line:10%
so the embers would stay
alive during the night.

00:44:01.350 --> 00:44:02.612 align:middle line:10%
She would go to bed.

00:44:02.612 --> 00:44:04.320 align:middle line:84%
She'd be the first
one up in the morning.

00:44:04.320 --> 00:44:06.997 align:middle line:10%
She'd take the embers
aside, blow on them,

00:44:06.997 --> 00:44:08.580 align:middle line:10%
and put new trough
in it, and the fire

00:44:08.580 --> 00:44:10.230 align:middle line:10%
would start right back up.

00:44:10.230 --> 00:44:12.930 align:middle line:10%
Now, that is what mysticism
has had to do in our world.

00:44:12.930 --> 00:44:15.810 align:middle line:84%
It's like there's been the
suppression of the embers

00:44:15.810 --> 00:44:17.700 align:middle line:90%
of the Holy Spirit.

00:44:17.700 --> 00:44:19.770 align:middle line:84%
And somehow, the
mystics of the world

00:44:19.770 --> 00:44:21.700 align:middle line:84%
have always managed
to go underground.

00:44:21.700 --> 00:44:25.030 align:middle line:84%
And Paul did a beautiful piece
in his last book on the Cathars

00:44:25.030 --> 00:44:27.010 align:middle line:90%
in 13th century Europe--

00:44:27.010 --> 00:44:29.875 align:middle line:84%
little groups who
kept the embers alive.

00:44:29.875 --> 00:44:32.500 align:middle line:84%
And that's what the mystics have
done throughout human history.

00:44:32.500 --> 00:44:35.590 align:middle line:84%
They're the mothers who put
the clinker and the fine ash

00:44:35.590 --> 00:44:39.370 align:middle line:84%
on the embers at night, when
the soldiers are passing by,

00:44:39.370 --> 00:44:41.620 align:middle line:84%
to take it away in the
morning, blow upon it,

00:44:41.620 --> 00:44:42.820 align:middle line:90%
and rekindle the fire.

00:44:42.820 --> 00:44:45.760 align:middle line:84%
And there were houses in Ireland
in which the fire literally

00:44:45.760 --> 00:44:48.160 align:middle line:90%
didn't go out for 300 years.

00:44:48.160 --> 00:44:50.860 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I've read that in
other books as well as yours.

00:44:50.860 --> 00:44:52.973 align:middle line:84%
That's a beautiful
metaphor for it.

00:44:52.973 --> 00:44:54.640 align:middle line:84%
We're going to toss
it to you now, Paul,

00:44:54.640 --> 00:44:55.930 align:middle line:90%
to make your final comments.

