00:45:08.200 --> 00:45:11.080 align:middle line:10%
But even within the
Popol Vuh, that's

00:45:11.080 --> 00:45:12.920 align:middle line:10%
not the explanation
of who we are.

00:45:12.920 --> 00:45:16.120 align:middle line:84%
They created something far
more able and beautiful

00:45:16.120 --> 00:45:17.500 align:middle line:90%
when they created us.

00:45:17.500 --> 00:45:20.860 align:middle line:84%
And when we start
reading ancestral stories

00:45:20.860 --> 00:45:24.280 align:middle line:84%
in the original languages,
as Sean was just describing,

00:45:24.280 --> 00:45:26.770 align:middle line:84%
suddenly, we discover
that some of our neighbors

00:45:26.770 --> 00:45:29.720 align:middle line:84%
come because they want
to be more like us.

00:45:29.720 --> 00:45:32.890 align:middle line:84%
They want what we have
in their gene pool.

00:45:32.890 --> 00:45:36.610 align:middle line:84%
I think there's something unique
about our heritage, our animal

00:45:36.610 --> 00:45:40.370 align:middle line:84%
heritage, our mammal
heritage, whatever

00:45:40.370 --> 00:45:43.180 align:middle line:84%
ET advantage we got
in that Mayan story

00:45:43.180 --> 00:45:46.790 align:middle line:84%
to create a species with a
unique capacity for love,

00:45:46.790 --> 00:45:49.720 align:middle line:84%
compassion,
creativity that makes

00:45:49.720 --> 00:45:51.280 align:middle line:90%
us attractive to our neighbors.

